In August 2008, domestic industrial sales prices increased by 0.1 per cent compared to the previous month, and 12.9 per cent compared to August 2007 - the Office of Statistics of Hungary reported.
Industrial export sales prices increased by 1.1 per cent in relation to those in July 2008, whereas compared to those in the previous year, they decreased by 3.9 per cent.
As a result of fluctuations in domestic prices and exports, industrial production prices increased by 0.7 per cent compared to those of the previous month and 3.2 per cent compared to those of the previous year.
Internal industrial sales prices have only increased to a lesser extent: 0.1 per cent, compared to the previous month.
The domestic sales prices in the processing industry increased only by 0.1 per cent by July.
In August 2008, the most significant price increase was observed in the leather and shoes manufacturing sector (2.8 per cent), with first place, the manufacture of bags and cents with a monthly increase of 4.6 per cent, then the production of shoes with 2.5 per cent of monthly increase.
The higher prices of the primary plastic and chemical materials resulted in a considerable monthly increase in the price of the product and chemical manufacturing sector (1.6 per cent).
A decrease resulted in oil transformation (1.4 per cent), the manufacture of machinery and electrical equipment (0.9 per cent), as well as a minimal increase in wood transformation (0.1 per cent).
The prices of paper production, publishing and printing activities have not changed.
The other sectors of the transformation industry recorded an increase of 0.2 per cent and 0.9 per cent.
In the sectors of electricity, gas, steam and water supply, which represent an important weight in national industrial operation, prices increased by 0.3 per cent in August, mainly due to the increase in gas prices by the authorities since 1 July.
In a 12-month comparison, taking into account the internal sales of the processing sectors, these are the prices of the oil processing sector which have known the most significant increase (32.4 per cent).
In the manufacturing of metallurgy products, an increase of 13.2 per cent was observed, while in the important area of food production, beverages and tobacco prices increased by 11 per cent.
Price reductions have been made in textile and textile production sectors (2.5 per cent), as well as in the manufacture of electrical machinery and equipment (0.3 per cent).
In the other sectors of the transformation industry, prices increased from 0.6 per cent to 9.1 per cent.
In the entire transformation industry, prices increased by 10.2 per cent during the school year.
The prices of electricity, gas, steam and water supply sectors exceeded 18.7 per cent of the previous year.
Among the internal trade groups and according to sectoral employment, in August, these are the investment initiatives that have shown the most significant monthly price increase (0.7 per cent).
In the production sectors of consumer goods, prices increased by 0.3 per cent, while those of the energy and material producing sectors for further transformation did not know any change over the previous month.
In August 2008, compared to the same month of the previous year, the most important increase in energy and material production sectors was observed in subsequent transformation (16.8 per cent).
In the production sectors of consumer goods, 6.8 per cent inflation has been achieved, while in the interest-initiators sectors, a decrease of 1.4 per cent has been observed.
The sales prices in the industrial sector in HUF increased by 1.1 per cent in August compared to the previous month, while they fell by 3.9 per cent by 12 months.
